# Acvilas Medical Management Software — User Manual

---

## Chapter 1: Home / Dashboard

The **Dashboard** is the first screen you see when you log in to Acvilas. It gives you a complete real-time overview of your clinic's daily activity.

---

### 1.1 Accessing the Dashboard

When you open Acvilas, you will be automatically directed to the **Home** screen. You can also return to it at any time by clicking **Home** in the left-side navigation menu (highlighted in purple when active).

---

### 1.2 Top Navigation Bar (Appointment Filter)

At the top right of the Dashboard, you will find the **All Appointment** filter panel. This allows you to:

- **Filter by Doctor** — By default it shows "All doctors selected." Click this to filter statistics for a specific doctor.
- **Filter by Date** — The date selector shows the current month (e.g., *April 2026*). Click the calendar icon to change the date range and view historical data.

---

### 1.3 Appointment Summary Cards

Just below the top bar, you will see **8 summary stat cards** that give you a quick count of all appointments for the selected period:

| Card | Color | What It Shows |
|---|---|---|
| **Total** | Grey | Total number of appointments |
| **Pending** | Orange | Appointments not yet actioned |
| **Attended** | Blue | Patients who have arrived |
| **Cancelled** | Red | Appointments that were cancelled |
| **Completed** | Green | Fully completed appointments |
| **Waiting** | Yellow | Patients currently waiting |
| **Revisit** | Purple | Patients scheduled for a follow-up |
| **Refunds** | Orange-Red | Refund transactions processed |

> **Tip:** These numbers update in real time. Click the **Refresh** link next to the Dashboard title to manually refresh the data.

---

### 1.4 Appointment Volume Chart

The left chart on the Dashboard displays **Appointment Volume** over the current month (Days 1–19 in the example).

- The **X-axis** represents the days of the month.
- The **Y-axis** represents the number of appointments.
- Each **colored line** represents a different appointment status:

| Color | Status |
|---|---|
| 🟡 Yellow | Pending |
| 🔵 Blue | Patient Attended |
| 🔴 Red | Cancelled |
| 🟢 Green | Completed |
| ⚫ Black | Waiting |
| 🟣 Purple | Revisit |
| 🟠 Orange | Pay Return |
| 🩷 Pink | Total |

Use this chart to **identify busy days**, spot trends, and manage staff scheduling.

---

### 1.5 Financial Stream Chart

The right chart displays the **Financial Stream** — income activity over the same date range.

- **APD** (shown in Yellow) — Appointment/service revenue
- **PROD** (shown in Blue) — Product/pharmacy sales revenue

Use this chart to monitor **daily revenue trends** and identify high-income days.

---

### 1.6 Left Side Navigation Menu

The vertical menu on the left provides access to all modules of the software:

| Menu Item | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Home** | Returns to this Dashboard |
| **OPD** | Outpatient Department management |
| **Appointment** | Create and view appointments |
| **App. Management** | Manage appointment settings |
| **Customers** | Patient/customer records |
| **Time Table** | Doctor schedules and availability |
| **Cashier** | Payment and billing counter |
| **Service Task** | Clinical service task tracking |
| **Invoice** | Generate and manage invoices |
| **TV Projector** | Display queue/info on waiting room screen |
| **Reports** | Generate operational and financial reports |
