# Chapter 2: OPD (Outpatient Department)

The **OPD module** is the core clinical workspace in Acvilas. It is where doctors see patients, record prescriptions, add services, dispense products, and complete consultations. Navigate to it by clicking **OPD** in the left sidebar.

---

## 2.1 OPD Screen Overview

At the top of the OPD screen you will see:

| Element | Description |
|---|---|
| **Doctor Name & Tagline** | Shows the active doctor (e.g., *Test Doctor*) |
| **Token No** | Displays the current patient token number. Use the **◀ ▶ arrows** to navigate between tokens |
| **Token Print** | Prints a physical token slip for the patient |
| **Session 1** | Indicates the current active session. Click to switch sessions if multiple are configured |
| **Today List** | Opens the full list of today's patients (see Section 2.6) |
| **Patient History** | Appears once a patient is loaded — shows the patient's past visit records |
| **Save** | Saves the current consultation record (orange button) |
| **Complete** | Marks the consultation as fully completed (green button) |

---

## 2.2 Finding / Loading a Patient

On the **right panel** under **Customer Information**, you can locate an existing patient using three methods:

### Option A — Search by Phone
1. Select the **Phone** radio button.
2. Type the patient's phone number in the search field.
3. The system will display matching patient records below.
4. Click the correct patient name to load their record.

### Option B — Search by User ID
1. Select the **User ID** radio button.
2. Type the patient's User ID (F2 shortcut to focus the field).
3. Select the matching record from the results list.

### Option C — ID Scan
1. Click the **ID Scan** button.
2. Scan the patient's ID using a connected scanner or camera.
3. The system will auto-fill and load the patient record.

> **Keyboard Shortcut:** Press **F2** to quickly jump to the User ID search field.

---

## 2.3 Adding a New Patient

If the patient does not exist in the system:

1. Click the **Add New** button (purple, top right of Customer Information panel).
2. Fill in the patient details in the form that appears.
3. Alternatively, click **Create New Record** (green button) that appears in the search results area after a failed search.
4. Enter optional fields such as **Age** and **City** in the Customer Data section.

> **Keyboard Shortcut:** Press **F8** or click **EMPTY CUSTOMER ENTRY (F8)** to quickly clear all fields and start a fresh patient entry.

---

## 2.4 Acvilas AI — Specialised Intelligence Panel

Once a patient is loaded, the **Acvilas AI** panel appears automatically in the main workspace area. This is an AI-powered clinical assistant built into the software.

### What it does:
- Automatically generates a **clinical summary** of the patient including chronic conditions, surgical history, allergies, current medications, and social history.
- Displays the summary across multiple pages (e.g., *1 / 6* — use the **◀ ▶** arrows to navigate pages).

### How to use it:
- Read the auto-generated summary at the top of the panel.
- Use the **"Ask about patient history…"** text box at the bottom to type a specific clinical question about the patient and press **Ask**.
- The AI will respond based on the patient's stored records.

> ⚠️ **Important Notice:** *Acvilas AI is not a real doctor — it is a helpful assistant only.* Always apply clinical judgment.

---

## 2.5 Consultation Record — Prescription Tab

Once a patient is selected and a token is assigned (Token No changes from 0 to 1, 2, etc.), the main consultation form becomes active. The default tab is **Prescription**.

### Clinical Fields:

| Field | Purpose |
|---|---|
| **Past Medical History** | Enter the patient's known medical background |
| **Presenting Complaint** | Enter the reason for today's visit |
| **Allergies** | Record any known drug or other allergies |
| **Treatments** | Note the treatment plan decided by the doctor |

### Outside Prescription (Drug Entry):

Use the table at the bottom of the Prescription tab to add medications:

| Column | What to Enter |
|---|---|
| **Drug Name** | Type the name of the medication |
| **Qty** | Enter the quantity to dispense |
| **Dosage** | Select or type the dose amount |
| **Frequency** | How often to take (e.g., twice daily) |
| **Days** | Number of days for the course |

After filling in each row, click the green **Add** button to add it to the prescription list.

### Other Prescription Tools:
- **Attachments** — Upload files from your computer (documents, lab results, images, photos, PDFs, etc.) to attach to this consultation record.
- **Print** — Print the prescription directly.
- **Make Template** — Save the current item list as a reusable template for future consultations.
- **Clear All Items** — Remove all added items from the current record.

---

## 2.6 Services Tab

Click the **Services** tab to add billable clinical services to the patient's visit.

- Use the **Search by Name, Title or Code** field to find a specific service.
- Filter services by responsible staff using the **All Doctors & Paramedicals** dropdown.

The services list shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Service Name** | The category of the service |
| **Title** | The specific service title |
| **CODE** | The service billing code |
| **Responsible** | Who performs the service (doctor/none) |
| **Res. Name** | The assigned staff member's name |
| **Task** | Whether a service task is created — **Yes** (green) or **No** (red) |
| **Total Price** | The charge for the service |
| **Option** | Click **Add** to attach the service to the patient's bill |

---

## 2.7 Templates Tab

Click **Templates** to load a previously saved consultation template. This is useful for common or recurring visit types (e.g., a standard consultation package), saving data entry time.

---

## 2.8 Products Tab

Click the **Products** tab to dispense pharmacy or clinic products directly from the OPD screen.

- Use the **(F9) Search by Generic, Code, or Name** field to quickly find a product.
- Click **Refresh** to reload the latest stock list.

The product list shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Generic Name** | The generic/chemical name of the product |
| **Code** | The stock/inventory code |
| **Name** | The brand name |
| **Unit Price** | The price per unit |
| **Quantity** | Current stock available (negative means stock adjustment needed) |
| **Option** | Click **Add** to add the product to the patient's bill |

---

## 2.9 Today List

Click the **Today List** button at the top of the OPD screen to open a popup showing all patients registered for the current day.

The list can be filtered using three tabs:

| Tab | Shows |
|---|---|
| **All** | Every patient registered today |
| **Pending** | Patients waiting to be seen |
| **In Progress** | Patients currently being consulted |
| **Complete** | Patients whose consultation is finished |

Each row in the list shows:

| Column | Description |
|---|---|
| **Token No** | The queue number assigned to the patient |
| **Record ID** | The system record ID |
| **Name** | Patient name |
| **Phone** | Patient contact number |
| **Status** | Current status (pending / in progress / complete) |
| **Load Record** | Click to open that patient's consultation in the OPD screen |
| **Remove** | Click to remove the patient from today's queue |

---

## 2.10 Attaching Files (Acvisync & Upload)

Within the Prescription tab, the **Attachments** button allows you to attach files to a patient's consultation record. Supported methods include:

- **Upload from Computer** — Click Attachments and browse your device to select and upload any file type (images, PDFs, lab reports, X-rays, documents, etc.).
- **Acvisync (Mobile Upload via QR Code)** — Acvilas supports a mobile sync option where you can scan a QR code on your phone to connect your mobile device and upload photos or files directly from your mobile camera or gallery into the patient's record wirelessly.

---

## 2.11 Completing a Consultation

Once all information has been entered:

1. Click **Save** (orange button) to save the record without closing it.
2. Click **Complete** (green button) to mark the consultation as done. This will move the patient's status to "Complete" in the Today List and update the Dashboard counters accordingly.

